1 Section 1. Section 81-1414.07, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 81-1414.07 (1)(a) In order to maintain his or her professional
4 status and serve the law enforcement profession, the community, and the
5 residents of Nebraska, each law enforcement officer, other than a
6 noncertified conditional officer, shall attend continuing education
7 courses for the number of hours required in subdivision (1)(b) of this
8 section in the areas of criminal justice and law enforcement during each
9 calendar year beginning on January 1 and ending on December 31. A law
10 enforcement officer is not required to meet the continuing education
11 requirements in the year in which he or she first becomes fully
12 certified. A law enforcement officer may retire from service in good
13 standing without meeting the continuing education requirements in the
14 calendar year of the officer's retirement.
15 (b) The number of continuing education hours required under this
16 subsection shall be the greater of:
17 (i) Until January 1, 2022, twenty hours;
18 (ii) Beginning January 1, 2022, and until January 1, 2023, twenty-
19 eight hours; and
20 (i) For a law enforcement officer serving in a county with a
21 population of forty thousand or more inhabitants as determined by the
22 most recent federal decennial census or the most recent revised certified
23 count by the United States Bureau of the Census, (iii) Beginning January
24 1, 2023, thirty-two hours; or .
25 (ii) For a law enforcement officer serving in a county with a
26 population of less than forty thousand inhabitants as determined by the
27 most recent federal decennial census or the most recent revised certified
28 count by the United States Bureau of the Census, twenty hours.
29 (c) For a law enforcement officer who is not employed but who wishes
30 to maintain such officer's professional status, the officer shall be
31 considered to serve in the county of the officer's residence for purposes
