1 of subdivision (1)(b) of this section.
2 (2) The annual continuing education required by this section shall
3 include:
4 (a) Refresher courses on de-escalation, mental health, and substance
5 abuse issues;
6 (b) A minimum of two hours of anti-bias and implicit bias training;
7 (c) Firearms;
8 (d) Officer wellness;
9 (e) Legal updates, including, but not limited to, legislative
10 changes and First Amendment and Fourth Amendment issues;
11 (f) Vehicular pursuit policy review; and
12 (g) Any other training as determined by a law enforcement agency.
13 (3) Continuing education courses may be offered in the form of
14 seminars, advanced education which may include college or university
15 classes, conferences, instruction conducted within the law enforcement
16 officer's law enforcement agency, or instruction conducted over the
17 Internet. Continuing education shall be of a type which has application
18 to and seeks to maintain and improve the skills of the law enforcement
19 officer in carrying out his or her duties and responsibilities.
20 Sec. 2. This act becomes operative on January 1, 2026.
21 Sec. 3. Original section 81-1414.07, Reissue Revised Statutes of
22 Nebraska, is repealed.
